# age key — EXAMPLE / PLACEHOLDER ONLY
# =====================================
# This file documents the shape of the age key used for SOPS decryption.
# It contains NO real key material and is safe to commit.
#
# NOTE: for the LOCAL demo, a throwaway key is ALREADY provided at
#
#     bootstrap/local/age.key
#
# (intentionally committed via a .gitignore exception) so `task up:local` works
# with zero key setup. It only decrypts the fake demo secrets in this repo.
# In AZURE mode the age key lives in Azure Key Vault and is NEVER committed.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Want your OWN key instead of the bundled demo key? (optional)
# 1) Generate it:
#
#       age-keygen -o bootstrap/local/age.key
#
#    age-keygen prints the PUBLIC recipient ("age1...") to stderr — put it into
#    the repo-root `.sops.yaml` `creation_rules`, then re-encrypt the secrets:
#       sops updatekeys apps/base/*/secret.sops.yaml infrastructure/configs/*/secret.sops.yaml
#
# 2) `task up:local` (or bootstrap/local/bootstrap.sh) loads the private key into
#    the cluster as Secret `sops-age` (key `age.agekey`) in namespace `flux-system`.
#    Flux's kustomize-controller uses it to decrypt *.sops.yaml on apply.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# A real age.key has exactly this structure (placeholders shown so secret
# scanners don't flag this example — your real key is git-ignored):
#
#   created: <timestamp>
#   public key: age1<58 lowercase base32 chars>
#   AGE-SECRET-KEY-1<58 uppercase base32 chars>   # <- the private key line
